The police command in Adamawa State has confirmed the release of Mr Hamidu Mijinyawa, the All Progressives Congress (APC) Chairman in Demsa Local Government Area. Mijinyawa was abducted in the early hours of Wednesday by some gunmen in Demsa, who later called demanding for N20 million ransom. Confirming the release, the command’s spokesman, SP Othman Abubakar, said the party chairman was released in the early hours of yesterday. Abubakar did not say whether ransom was paid or not. “All I can tell you for now is that Mijinyawa has been released by the kidnappers,” Abubakar said. Also confirming the release, State Publicity Secretary of the APC, Alhaji Mohammed Abdullahi, said Mijinyawa was hale and hearty. “He is out hale and hearty and is now with his family,” Abdullahi said. (NAN)  Gunmen kidnap APC chairman in Adamawa Gunmen kidnap Adamawa APC official Gunmen kidnap 27-year-old businessman in Sokoto – NSCDC